\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 33
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 And after they had stayed there for a time, they were sent back with greetings from the brethren to the apostles. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 34
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 However, it seemed good to Silas to remain there.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 35
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Paul and Barnabas also remained in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 the Lord, with many others also. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 36
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Then after some days Paul said to Barnabas, "Let us now go back and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the Lord, and see how they are doing." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 37
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Now Barnabas was determined to take with them John called Mark. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 38
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But Paul insisted that they should not take with them the one who had departed from them in Pamphylia, and had not gone with them to the work. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 39
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Then the contention became so sharp that they parted from one another. And so Barnabas took Mark and sailed to Cyprus; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 40
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 but Paul chose Silas and departed, being commended by the brethren to the grace of God. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 41
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 And he went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.\uc0\u8232 
\b\fs64 \cf4 16
\b0\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 Then he came to Derbe and Lystra. And behold, a certain disciple was there, 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 named Timothy, the son of a certain Jewish woman who believed, but his father was Greek. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He was well spoken of by the brethren who were at Lystra and Iconium. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Paul wanted to have him go on with him. And he took him and circumcised him because of the Jews who were in that region, for they all knew that his father was Greek. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 And as they went through the cities, they delivered to them the decrees to keep, which were determined by the apostles and elders at Jerusalem. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 So the churches were strengthened in the faith, and increased in number daily. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Now when they had gone through Phrygia and the region of Galatia, they were 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

